Shortly after his release from jail, 26-year-old Ismaila Sikirullahi has found his way back. Sikirullahi was on Monday sentenced to one-year imprisonment by an Osun State Magistratesâ€™ Court sitting in Osogbo for burglary and stealing. Police prosecutor Kayode Adeoye said Sikirullahi broke into the shop of one Azeez Anifat and stole a purse containing one Itel mobile phone and a cash sum of N8,360. Sikirullahi, who did not have legal representation, pleaded guilty to the two counts. Inspector Kayode said that he was an ex-convict and just finished a jail term for a similar offence. The Magistrate, Mr Adebayo Ajala sentenced him to one-year imprisonment without an option of fine.